It's not a game of complicated transformations and collisions, but if you have no idea what you're going to do with an object, how your car is going to behave, something's wrong.
Usually when you drive or drive by cars in a dense stream, you sometimes touch a different car slightly, but sometimes, in almost the same situation, your car starts to break apart.
Or the buckets were broken.
It's not important because of a restarting system, but it's enough to ruin fun.
The restarts are arranged so that if you break or leave the highway far away, the game will bring you back to the point where it's interrupted.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you're using them all, you're going to have to start the race from the start.
It's useful if something doesn't work, but you can't rely on it completely.
