It doesn't matter what doesn't let you miss -- the concept of fifty unique tracks, the sequence of races, or something else.
The idea of changing cars during a race is unusual.
You need to track the gas station because it's where your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports machines are suitable for cities; powerful U.S. cars are for direct cuts of highways; and exotic super-decks for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain tracks.
The main mode mode is closely related to challenge mode; it is a race on individual sites that you will find out during the course of the game.
