You and your car enter the subway tunnel (let's say you're) where you're running through the rails in the dark (let's say you are).
Your speedometer shows the figures from 150 to 200 km/h (let's say you are) when the subway train suddenly arrives behind you, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
For a few days, our version has been discussing whether no one thought at the time of the game's creation, or whether its creators really think we're so daft.
