Although it is regrettable that in some critical moments the quality of the recording is sometimes quite high, it is declining.
This is especially true of incidents involving a large number of participants, where a good recording would not be of particular help to you.
The sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the lover.
To please the widest possible audience of young people, the soundtrack's music came from different styles; but it is unlikely that many people will buy a game because of its music.
The general impression of Need for Speed: The escape is rather disorderly.
If the game were to avoid obviously unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that the escape is the best part of the NFS over the last few years.
