It's an excerpt from a conversation that has full decryption on-line in The Nation.
For your Costa Rican fans, it's a dream that Pearl Jam will play Costa Rica?
A trip to Costa Rica is a dream that has come true for us too.
This is just our second visit to South and Central America, and it's still going well.
I was only in Costa Rica once on vacation, it's a beautiful country, and I think we can stay there for a few days.
So we're very happy to bring our music there.
I ask this because there's some loyalty to the group; fans live in tension the days before the concert.
What do you say to your most devoted fans?
Thank you for having been with us all these years.
