Looking at the tour, you might say that you've made grand shows with lots of songs.
What did you plan to do in Costa Rica?
Since we've never played there before, we don't have any restrictions on what we can do.
We're going to try to make the best show out of the most diverse songs possible; we're going to try to play several songs from every album and present our fans with a great variety of repertoires.
You never repeat the repertoire.
How do you do that?
I think it's partly because we have nine plates and we can play more than 120 songs, and everyone likes different songs, so it's hard to choose which songs to play every night.
When we have two or three songs that we haven't played for a while, it keeps us in the tone and surprises us because it reminds us of the reasons why we loved those songs and that we might forget.
